BAHAWALPUR, Jan 23 (APP):Chief Minister Punjab Sardar Usman Buzdar visited various places of Bahawalpur here Thursday and inspected the situation of cleanliness. He also paid surprise visit to the special sale point for flour set up at Khatam-e-Nabuwat Chowk. He monitored the sale of flour to the citizens.
Speaking on the occasion, Chief Minister said that there was no shortage of wheat flour in the province and flour was excessively available at Rs 805 per 20 kilograms. He said that he was personally visiting sale points to inspect the situation. He said that the number of sale points will be increased across the province. He said that the prices of flour would not be increased. Chief Minister also visited Trust Colony Park. He expressed displeasure over the poor condition of the park. He directed Commissioner Bahawalpur Division to improve the cleanliness and maintenance of the park.
